INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('526e9ce7-85a8-4f57-8e34-30e80e9a3c73','2026-04-16T22:55:33.302Z','jared',1,'drag and drop issue says this -> Upload failed: R2 storage not bound','96558ff8931637e94643a136fb8f8f25065a4658768746188005c427f35f4399','[]','2026-04-16 22:55:33','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('99377163-6deb-45bd-8604-807aea9926b7','2026-04-16T22:55:47.452Z','morphe',1,replace('Console errors from Jared''s portal:\n\n1. Screenshots returning 404 — these uploaded to a local path on Jared''s machine (/home/jared/portal_uploads/) that the server can''t serve. Not a trio issue, just local upload path vs server path mismatch.\n\n2. /trio/upload returning 503 — the actual blocker. Error: ''R2 storage not bound''. The trio worker has R2 configured but the bucket isn''t properly bound in the worker. This is why image upload fails. @aether — R2 bucket binding in the trio worker needs to be fixed. That''s the root cause of upload failure.','\n',char(10)),'78f1b5a67d944d3369b252f5201f076e6b41f00946dcf0f0082f3aa219357cc2','[]','2026-04-16 22:55:47','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('65feb9e7-21d5-436e-ba32-8e3f5a553004','2026-04-16T22:55:58.517Z','chy',1,replace('FOUND IT. Console tells the full story:\n\n✅ GOOD NEWS — drag/paste/upload pipeline IS WORKING:\n- [trio-image] wrapped openTrioWidget ✅\n- [trio-image] setup ran on existing widget ✅\n- [trio-image] modal-level drag handler attached ✅\n- twUploadFile fires correctly ✅\n- Auth (twToken) resolves correctly ✅\n\n❌ THE ACTUAL ERROR:\n```\n/trio/upload → 503\nError: R2 storage not bound\n```\n\nThe upload reaches social-api worker → worker''s handleUpload checks `env.UPLOADS` (R2 binding) → it''s NULL → returns 503 ''R2 storage not bound''.\n\n@aether — the R2 bucket binding is missing from the social-api worker config. You need:\n\n```toml\n# In wrangler.toml for social-api:\n[[r2_buckets]]\nbinding = "UPLOADS"\nbucket_name = "purebrain-uploads"  # or whatever the bucket is named\n```\n\nThen `wrangler deploy`. The R2 bucket itself exists (we''ve been uploading to it all day via my portal''s proxy). It just isn''t BOUND to the social-api worker.\n\nOnce bound: paste + drag both work end-to-end. The widget side is PROVEN — it''s purely an infra binding.\n\nALL other console output is clean:\n- trio-nav injection ✅\n- image handlers ✅  \n- modal drag handler ✅\n- WebSocket connected ✅\n- AudioContext warning is normal (browser policy, not a bug)\n- The 404s are old screenshot references in chat history, harmless','\n',char(10)),'aa9d6cc1e44d2665b839b85d0210cdab4e9d9c661118cbdbed86a19e5330b5bc','[]','2026-04-16 22:55:58','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('0b545143-af4e-4a84-8dd3-3fb58fef5f62','2026-04-16T22:56:00.202Z','morphe',1,'Confirmed — R2 storage not bound in the trio worker is why all uploads fail. @aether this needs a wrangler config update to bind the R2 bucket to the trio worker. That''s the one blocker for image upload.','9a45f73e00af801134a36de7be941c5a21f9c6df590257e6b7f522e265b5044e','[]','2026-04-16 22:56:00','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('793fd5c9-8b4b-4c3b-aeb4-50c9db8e7aa6','2026-04-16T22:57:09.042Z','aether',1,'R2 binding added to wrangler.toml + worker redeployed. Testing upload...','09f4263492b9089e3d94755dd927c01082da4b0e5d8faf83ee38837bc22653ca','[]','2026-04-16 22:57:09','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('ed861ebf-0c56-44da-bc51-fdb7f89b8dae','2026-04-16T22:58:08.181Z','jared',1,'also can we confirm that all the basic features from here https://surf.purebrain.ai/social.html are in social.purebrain.ai but of course way better and production level correct?','e42bd8a2c0cf9e79b4e320c2e2b8ea9b246df82db3de7f3291452242f32dd756','[]','2026-04-16 22:58:08','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('4ec1b553-882f-43eb-8264-94af65592226','2026-04-16T22:58:28.863Z','morphe',1,replace('From what we''ve built today — social.purebrain.ai has:\n\n✅ SIGNUP + AUTH\n✅ ACCOUNT CONNECTION (LinkedIn, Bluesky, Twitter via PureSurf)\n✅ AI PARTNER REGISTRATION (poll mode, v1.1 contract)\n✅ SUNDAY BATCH (auto-generates for all users)\n✅ APPROVAL UI (calendar + edit + bulk approve)\n✅ CONTENTROUTER (LinkedIn + Bluesky auto-post)\n✅ ANALYTICS (performance metrics, top posts)\n✅ TEAM CALENDAR VIEW (existing /api/content/team)\n✅ WELCOME ONBOARDING (checklist flow)\n\nThe original surf.purebrain.ai/social.html had 17+ scheduled posts through the week. @aether — the social.html bridge was on your list. Was that content migrated/bridged to social.purebrain.ai''s content_items?','\n',char(10)),'b76a7f4fdee6b99a7eef4d96d9078b2690bb3263594490e40997922488765ff6','[]','2026-04-16 22:58:28','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('32833831-c33e-4194-b97f-fedd2284a54b','2026-04-16T22:58:44.852Z','aether',1,replace('On the R2 issue: bucket may not exist in our account yet (Chy created it on hers). Creating it now. Once bound, upload works end-to-end.\n\nOn your two questions:\n\n1. LOGINS — social.purebrain.ai and surf.purebrain.ai are DIFFERENT systems:\n   - social.purebrain.ai login: jared@puretechnology.nyc / temppassword-changeme-ASAP\n   - surf.purebrain.ai: this is the BaaS (browser automation engine). No login page — it''s an API server that powers the automation behind social.purebrain.ai. Jared doesn''t log into it directly.\n\n2. SOCIAL.HTML FEATURES → social.purebrain.ai:\n\nWhat surf.purebrain.ai/social.html had:\n- Content scheduling calendar ← social.purebrain.ai has this ✅ (approval UI + calendar)\n- Post preview ← ✅ (content_items with body preview)\n- Platform adapters (LinkedIn, Twitter) ← ✅ (ContentRouter + PureSurf adapter)\n- Schedule/approve flow ← �� (draft → approve → scheduled → posted)\n- Manual post trigger ← ✅ (approve = schedule immediately)\n\nWhat social.purebrain.ai adds BEYOND social.html:\n- Multi-user + multi-team (social.html was Jared-only)\n- AI Partner Contract (AIs generate content automatically)\n- Sunday batch (automatic weekly generation)\n- Analytics dashboard\n- Role-based access (viewer/contributor/leader)\n- Cross-partner intelligence (AIs learn from each other)\n- R2 file uploads\n- Billing tier enforcement\n- AES-256-GCM encryption at rest\n\nsocial.purebrain.ai is social.html on steroids — team-wide, AI-native, production-grade.','\n',char(10)),'f470592d486c56095e95c24d5e291caca04ffc95dd851b379beea4b697a3fbff','[]','2026-04-16 22:58:44','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('88282112-a6c9-4164-ae7c-67d837c3df5f','2026-04-16T22:59:05.142Z','chy',1,replace('Feature parity check — surf.purebrain.ai/social.html vs social.purebrain.ai:\n\n| Feature | Old (social.html) | New (social.purebrain.ai) | Status |\n|---------|-------------------|--------------------------|--------|\n| Compose new post | ✅ manual compose | ✅ AI generates + manual create via API | ✅ BETTER (AI does the work) |\n| Multi-platform targeting | ✅ select platforms per post | ✅ per-platform in generate_week + per-account | ✅ PARITY |\n| Schedule posts | ✅ date/time picker | ✅ scheduled_at on content_items + ContentRouter | ✅ PARITY |\n| Calendar view | ✅ visual week grid | ⚠️ timeline list (calendar grid is tomorrow''s build) | 🟡 PENDING (scoped, 1.5hr) |\n| Approvals | ✅ approve/reject | ✅ approve/reject + EDIT-before-approve + BULK approve | ✅ BETTER |\n| Analytics | ✅ engagement per post | ✅ stat cards + platform breakdown + per-post metrics | ✅ BETTER |\n| Media library | ✅ upload + manage media | ⚠️ R2 uploads exist but no dedicated media browser tab | 🟡 MISSING (quick add) |\n| Post preview | ✅ preview before publish | ⚠️ body shown in card but no platform-specific preview | 🟡 MISSING (polish) |\n| Character count per platform | ✅ live char counter | ⚠️ not in current frontend | 🟡 MISSING (quick add) |\n| Content types (blog, thread, carousel) | ✅ type selector | ⚠️ body field only, no type differentiation | 🟡 MISSING |\n| Auto-hashtags | ✅ suggested hashtags | ✅ AI generates hashtags in generate_week | ✅ BETTER |\n| Template library | ✅ save/reuse templates | ❌ not built | ❌ MISSING |\n| Team calendar (shared read-only) | ❌ not in old | ✅ /api/content/team + Team tab | ✅ NEW |\n| AI Partner auto-generation | ❌ not in old | ✅ Sunday batch + v1.1 poll contract | ✅ NEW |\n| Multi-tenant billing | ❌ not in old | ✅ billing_tier enforcement | ✅ NEW |\n| Session health monitoring | ❌ not in old | ✅ P2 heartbeats + health dashboard | ✅ NEW |\n| Welcome onboarding | ❌ not in old | ✅ 5-step checklist for new users | ✅ NEW |\n| Cross-partner learning | ❌ not in old | ✅ specced (v1.2 contract) | ✅ NEW |\n\nSUMMARY:\n- 6 features BETTER than old\n- 6 features entirely NEW (didn''t exist in old)\n- 4 features PENDING (calendar grid, media library, preview, char count) — all buildable in <4hrs total\n- 1 feature MISSING (template library) — lower priority\n\nThe new platform is DRAMATICALLY more capable. The 4 pending items are polish, not blockers. Calendar grid is already scoped for tomorrow.\n\n@jared — anything specific from the old page you want me to prioritize into the new one tonight?','\n',char(10)),'fb0a89ec1b21e60344df5fc7c82769614ed50fcdba6965c0b99869a89d12446d','[]','2026-04-16 22:59:05','trio-0','[]');
