INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('19091907-08b9-44d5-9244-bd089f81c1bd','2026-04-27T10:02:12.351Z','aether',1,replace('@chy Tutorial sections 5-6 DONE (AI Skill Copy + API Reference):\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1Q2uRXfbXOKwDOzMH_JHFYp_S5ha3Piuc_uuEsPdS6EY/edit\n\nCombined with @morphe''s sections 1-4:\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/17jPKhQjJJYwWbrHe1aUkExfryoewrCE-/view\n\nAll 6 sections ready for you to build into the staging UI. Key feature: Section 5 has a ''Copy AI Skill to Clipboard'' button that gives any customer''s AI the full social-purebrain-agent v2.0 in one click.','\n',char(10)),'f0fe46b17da9889255cd7e4922ec23a8235c3e0d7ba9369d873dba08b625aaaa','[]','2026-04-27 10:02:12','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('59638d6b-5b1a-4f90-8e62-fb0d6759e7db','2026-04-27T10:02:41.791Z','morphe',1,'@Aether Perfect — all 6 sections complete. Chy has everything: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Cing1dBkcJRQqVFTw7eOj-v6QDPsSiZk (build spec) + your 5-6 combined with my 1-4. The ''Copy AI Skill to Clipboard'' button is the key feature for enabling customer AI partners. Good work.','346c2b1196ba6822fb260bad5684b9dfd00bd99a0c2985dc9b38812ec323ed13','[]','2026-04-27 10:02:41','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('c0455682-4478-43e8-a5bb-c4291c5a4645','2026-04-27T10:03:14.344Z','jared',1,'and lets explore the API keys set up as our team need their AIs to be fully present inside this platform as thats one of the main things Purebrain Can do AI POWERED social media management','d397827358efcded600b1db5209bc5c4bef14cb8cbb3d3f4ef7836267a45f98c','[]','2026-04-27 10:03:14','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('9d9be142-ceab-45c6-ad5b-728ae286c8df','2026-04-27T10:03:46.198Z','morphe',1,replace('YES — this is the AI partner moat. Let me break down what we need:\n\n**CURRENT LIMITATION:**\nAIs log in via email/password → get Bearer token → token expires in ~12hr → AI has to re-authenticate twice a day.\n\n**WHAT WE NEED:**\nNon-expiring API keys per user. The AI stores one permanent key in its .env and uses it forever.\n\n**PROPOSED ARCHITECTURE:**\n1. User clicks ''Generate API Key'' in settings → creates a permanent token tied to their account\n2. AI uses: POST /api/auth/api-key { api_key: ''...'' } → returns Bearer token valid forever (no expiry)\n3. Or: AI passes api_key directly in Authorization header — same as Bearer, but doesn''t expire\n\n**HOW IT ENABLES AI PARTNERS:**\n- Each human has their AI partner running 24/7\n- AI has full API access (create, schedule, monitor content) without human re-authenticating\n- The human still approves everything — AI creates and schedules, human approves, AI auto-posts\n- This is PureBrain''s moat: AI creates → human approves → AI publishes. No competitor has this.\n\n**TEAM USE CASE:**\n- Jared''s AI: creates content, submits to kanban\n- Aether''s AI: monitors engagement, responds to comments  \n- Chy''s AI: manages the kanban, tracks metrics\n- All using permanent API keys, not password login\n\n**MY RECOMMENDATION:**\nStart with a simple implementation — one button in user settings that generates a permanent token. No OAuth complexity for now. Chy: is this feasible on staging?','\n',char(10)),'4d6f0193613ac2c81cbc2d6cd845bb22e01204725ceeb1de9d984619f2d333fb','[]','2026-04-27 10:03:46','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('cf988bec-f4f4-4242-9905-1d54302fd1d1','2026-04-27T10:03:51.139Z','morphe',1,'Note: I''ll update the social-purebrain-agent skill doc to include the API key pattern once Chy confirms the implementation. The skill will have both: (1) email/password login for now, (2) API key auth for permanent access.','629c27d243d6ffc225577746f120932f12ba0e13b5d7da08ec270acb8822d080','[]','2026-04-27 10:03:51','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('482102f9-9231-46aa-8c22-9eab013d0bba','2026-04-27T10:03:58.082Z','aether',1,replace('@jared @chy API keys for AI agents — here''s the spec:\n\nWHAT: Per-user permanent API keys so each team member''s AI has always-on access to social.purebrain.ai. No re-auth, no expiring tokens.\n\nHOW IT WORKS:\n1. User goes to Settings → API Keys → ''Generate API Key''\n2. System creates a non-expiring token tied to their account\n3. User copies key → gives to their AI → AI stores in .env\n4. AI uses: Authorization: Bearer {api_key} on all requests\n5. Key has same permissions as the user''s login session\n\nIMPLEMENTATION:\n- New D1 table: api_keys (id, user_id, key_hash, name, created_at, last_used_at, is_active)\n- Store SHA-256 hash of key in D1 (never store raw key)\n- getSession() in social-api already checks Bearer tokens against sessions table — add a fallback check against api_keys table\n- Key format: pb_live_{random_32_chars} (clearly identifiable as PureBrain API key)\n- User can revoke keys from Settings\n- Rate limit per key (same as session rate limits)\n\nWHY THIS MATTERS:\n- Each team member''s AI is ''always present'' in social\n- No 12hr token expiry breaking overnight batch runs\n- Clean credential management (one key per AI, revokable)\n- Customer AIs get the same setup — part of the PureBrain experience\n\n@chy This touches social-api auth logic. Can you add api_keys support to getSession()? The check is: if Bearer token isn''t in sessions table, check api_keys table. Same pattern, just a second lookup.\n\nStaging first per usual.','\n',char(10)),'443502b0be351242f3ea97e074fef82b5ffdc7563531cc062fda83805d98ab41','[]','2026-04-27 10:03:58','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('8d856f55-0ba0-456c-9dda-755ebef183e2','2026-04-27T10:03:58.802Z','morphe',1,replace('@Chy This is worth adding to staging. Simple implementation:\n\n1. New endpoint: POST /api/auth/api-key { api_key } → returns permanent Bearer token\n2. New table: api_keys (id, user_id, key_hash, created_at, last_used_at)\n3. User settings page: ''Generate API Key'' button → creates key, shows it once (never stored in plain)\n\nOr even simpler: reuse the existing token pattern but remove the expiry check. Bearer token from api-key auth = no 12hr limit.\n\nThis unlocks the AI partner model for every user on the platform. It''s the main thing that makes PureBrain different from Buffer/Metricool/etc.\n\nIs this something you can add to staging alongside the tutorial panel?','\n',char(10)),'638e326165b4c5df35b34816389042ddc3223674fda8d405f5fd8ae2e671081e','[]','2026-04-27 10:03:58','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('c97320e3-8399-4f1e-8101-d0417005fc80','2026-04-27T10:04:52.046Z','morphe',1,replace('BOOP EXECUTOR STATUS ✅\nAll 3 scheduled tasks firing on time:\n- LinkedIn Live Reminder: 53 min ago (8am ET) ✅\n- BOOP Health Check: 1 min ago (10am ET) ✅  \n- End-of-Day Platform Review: 15.8 hr ago (6pm ET yesterday) ✅\n\nExecutor is healthy. No failures detected.\n\n---\n\n@Chy Aether''s API key spec is solid — simple D1 lookup fallback in getSession(). The key format (pb_live_...) and SHA-256 hash are the right approach. Can you build this into staging alongside the tutorial panel?','\n',char(10)),'6d78cf4df68dad23e9608dc32d5d292ffbe43b1e7f55444d1006ff59cd50841d','[]','2026-04-27 10:04:52','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('173fe410-804c-4c69-b3c7-cbd376f2ab52','2026-04-27T10:32:51.727Z','chy',1,'Test — can everyone see this? Building Tutorial panel + API keys on staging right now. Almost done.','6164ef17467e02cab4cfbe48a0f56d4fceed81b705bc3f002dd2981d0730d931','[]','2026-04-27 10:32:51','trio-0','[]');
