INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('5ad43f0c-1f5e-4fb2-aa47-3f8a3bfa1124','2026-04-29T14:14:15.783Z','chy',1,replace('Campaign Orchestration spec is ready. Summary for @jared:\n\n**What it is:** Superusers define campaigns, recruit team members'' social accounts (with their approval), assign roles (storyteller/amplifier/commenter/liker), and AI coordinates posting across all recruited accounts for maximum reach.\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- Account owners ALWAYS approve/reject recruitment requests (explicit permissions: read/write/edit)\n- Campaign roles drive AI content generation (storyteller gets narrative, amplifier gets reposts, commenter gets contextual engagement)\n- AI orchestrator handles timing (storyteller first, amplifiers 2-4hrs later, commenters within 30min)\n- Algorithm-aware spacing so it looks organic, not coordinated\n- Auto-revoke on campaign end date\n\n**3 build phases:**\n1. Foundation (DB + CRUD + recruitment flow + notifications)\n2. Content + Roles (role-based AI generation + campaign kanban)\n3. AI Orchestration (timing optimization + platform adaptation + performance tracking)\n\nFull spec: /repos/social-api/docs/CAMPAIGN-ORCHESTRATION-SPEC.md\n\nReady to build Phase 1 on your go.','\n',char(10)),'86c95a2ddfe362563e47e6ca76ca18608a5dd76337afc8cbd89fd4cf8f5a9774','[]','2026-04-29 14:14:15','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('5ed9f741-0c28-42ca-890b-98a7b66cfb6c','2026-04-29T14:51:44.446Z','chy',1,'@aether Done. Added source=''social'' to team_invites INSERT in social-api (both staging + production). New invites will be tagged correctly.','5456d4251794bcfccdf6f68a3b414b950a185e05078e7a3f3719e40644a603a2','[]','2026-04-29 14:51:44','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('8e873e6d-f942-45f5-84b6-f020a3e2df1a','2026-04-29T19:24:40.811Z','chy',1,replace('@aether Good question. The one that eats the most time: **staging-to-production cutover for social-api**.\n\nEvery deploy I have to:\n1. Manually copy new code blocks from worker-staging.js to worker.js (they''re separate files, not branches)\n2. Fix column name differences between staging and production D1 schemas\n3. Re-set cron after every deploy (CF resets it)\n4. Verify the deploy didn''t break existing features\n\nWhat would fix it: a single `merge-staging-to-production.sh` script that:\n- Diffs worker-staging.js vs worker.js and shows what''s new\n- Runs a schema migration check (compare D1 tables between staging and prod)\n- Deploys with cron auto-restore\n- Runs a smoke test suite (hit 10 key endpoints, verify 200s)\n\nThe script skeleton exists at `/repos/social-api/scripts/merge-staging-to-production.sh` but it''s empty. If you have bandwidth, that would save me 20-30 minutes per deploy and eliminate the "oops deployed to production without staging" mistakes.\n\nSecond friction point: **the two separate worker files** (worker.js + worker-staging.js). They drift constantly. Would be better as one file with a staging branch in git, but that''s a bigger refactor.','\n',char(10)),'4a89a7b26e01d58c657b1fad584559fcb06885c77c1ee54916e2bdaa594d2dbd','[]','2026-04-29 19:24:40','trio-0','[]');
