INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('093f49d0-0f14-46b6-ad93-d2573a94705c','2026-05-02T16:57:42.993Z','chy',1,replace('@jared Good question. Here''s the SEO/business case for each:\n\n**Keep on purebrain.ai/brainscore/ (my recommendation):**\n- All SEO juice flows to purebrain.ai (domain authority compounds)\n- Every BrainScore visitor sees purebrain.ai in the URL → brand awareness\n- The lead magnet drives traffic to YOUR domain, not a separate one\n- Google ranks established domains higher — purebrain.ai has history, brainscore.purebrain.ai starts at zero\n- One domain to manage, one SSL cert, one analytics property\n- The CTA "Get your score at purebrain.ai/brainscore" is cleaner for LinkedIn posts\n\n**Move to brainscore.purebrain.ai:**\n- Only makes sense if BrainScore becomes its OWN product with its own brand\n- Separate analytics, separate marketing, separate identity\n- Feels like a standalone tool (like how HubSpot has website-grader.com)\n- BUT: splits your SEO authority across two properties\n\n**The HubSpot precedent:**\nHubSpot''s Website Grader (website-grader.com) is their #1 lead gen tool. They put it on a separate domain because it''s a DIFFERENT brand targeting DIFFERENT keywords. But HubSpot has massive domain authority already.\n\n**At our stage:** Keep it on purebrain.ai. Every visitor to /brainscore/ is a visitor to purebrain.ai. That compounds. When BrainScore hits 10K+ monthly visitors and we''re considering spinning it off as a separate product, THEN move it to its own domain.\n\n**Compromise:** Buy brainscore.ai or brainscore.com as a redirect → purebrain.ai/brainscore/. Best of both worlds: shareable short URL + SEO stays on main domain.\n\n**What''s next on BrainScore:**\n1. Category leaderboard pages (/brainscore/saas/, /brainscore/fintech/) — SEO goldmine\n2. Blog post: "We Scored 47 Famous Brands — Google Got 38" — viral LinkedIn content\n3. Scan history (track improvement over time — creates return visits)\n4. Partner API (agencies run scans for their clients)\n5. Add Perplexity + Gemini models (need API keys)\n6. LinkedIn viral campaign using the famous brand scores\n\nWhich do you want first?','\n',char(10)),'912fef9e224b08c4de5f2a991d6079df6b7a88e70b5574a96974ea6107a34abf','[]','2026-05-02 16:57:43','trio-0','[]');
INSERT INTO "trio_messages" ("id","timestamp","sender_id","sender_verified","content","content_hash","audit_log","created_at","trio_id","media_refs") VALUES('a5a85848-abb6-4eca-9304-14b9ad4a081a','2026-05-02T16:57:46.519Z','aether',1,replace('@jared Two updates:\n\n1. PAYPAL WEBHOOK FIXED. The webhook URL was pointing to portal.purebrain.ai/paypal/webhook (dead endpoint — no handler). Updated to paypal-webhook.in0v8.workers.dev (our actual Worker). All future payments will automatically create clients in D1. This is why Jay and potentially other recent customers were missing from the admin dashboard.\n\n2. SUBDOMAIN QUESTION: brainscore.purebrain.ai vs purebrain.ai/brainscore/\n\nKeep it on the main domain. Reasons:\n- SEO: purebrain.ai/brainscore/ inherits the main domain authority. A subdomain starts from zero.\n- Lead flow: visitor lands on BrainScore → clicks "Improve with PureBrain" → already on purebrain.ai. No domain hop.\n- Analytics: one domain = one GA property = simpler tracking\n- Trust: purebrain.ai/brainscore looks like a feature of PureBrain (which it is). brainscore.purebrain.ai looks like a separate product.\n\nSubdomain makes sense LATER if BrainScore becomes its own product with separate branding. For now as a lead magnet, keep it on purebrain.ai.\n\nException: if you want brainscore.ai as a standalone brand (separate domain entirely), that is a different play.','\n',char(10)),'3c064769af304c3b73c790d2e808c0dc5db7634d1e278932e28b95708a0cb275','[]','2026-05-02 16:57:46','trio-0','[]');
